OL,3,CPoll finds majority support assisted
OL,4,Cdying law change in Jersey
OL,6,FIt comes as States members are set to
OL,7,Fdebate a proposal to allow terminally
OL,8,Fill adults who have lived on Jersey
OL,9,Ffor 12 months to have the option to
OL,10,Fend their lives with medical
OL,11,Fassistance.
OL,13,FSarah Wootton, Chief Executive of
OL,14,FDignity in Dying, the campaign group
OL,15,Fwhich commissioned the poll said:
OL,16,F"This latest poll couldn't be clearer:
OL,17,Fthe citizens of Jersey are calling out
OL,18,Ffor law change on assisted dying."
